</td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Proposed Loot System</span><hr size=1> Good idea that the loot rules section is admin postable only Neaadan.  One thing about that section that I would like to see also is that it is the law when it comes to looting.  Anywho, since that section is admin only, I will post the proposed system here and we can discuss and modify it until we decide to ratify it.<br>
------------------------------------------------------------<br>
1. Alliance members will recieve 3 points per raid the attend, invites will recieve 1 point per raid they attend. To be a raid that is counted for points, it must be officially posted on a message board and all alliance guilds must be informed about it. The raid must also require 3 or more groups to pull off, this is to prevent people sheduling small one group raids on zones just to get points.  Points will be recieved at the discresion of the raid leaders and loot coordinators.  This is to prevent people for showing up to a raid for one hour and expecting to get full points.  In situations like that partial points should be rewarded.  In cases where people stay for at least 3 hours, full points should be awarded however.<br>
<br>
1a.  Everyone will start with 6 points.<br>
<br>
1b.  Points will be awarded at the end of the raid to prevent people who plan on showing up for 1 hour to recive full points to spend on armors.<br>
<br>
2. There will be no penatly for missing raids other than that you dont get the points for the raid and will have to wait longer to get points to spend on loot.<br>
<br>
3. Point Costs<br>
<br>
The old world planes: <br>
Brestplates and legs=4 points<br>
All other pieces=2 points<br>
Planar weapon=3 points<br>
<br>
Quest Armors (kael and such):<br>
Breastplate and legs=6points<br>
All other pieces=3 points<br>
Other items=3 points<br>
<br>
Non planar raids:<br>
Weapons=2 points<br>
Armors/items=2 points<br>
<br>
Epic Pieces:<br>
No points will be spent on epic loots, they go to person farthest along, if there is a dispute over who is farthest along, it will go to ther person with the most seniority in the class.<br>
<br>
Dragon loot=5 points per piece. Only one piece per raid.<br>
<br>
4. If two people wish to buy the same piece of loot, priortiy will be given to the one who has the most seniority in the class. Only one piece of loot can be boughten until everyone of the spoken class who has the points to get loot has purchased an item.  If a dispute over seniority in the class arises, the person with the most points will recieve the item.<br>
<br>
4a.  If the situation arises that no one has points to buy an item such as a breastplate, the person with the most seniority in the class can spend whatever points they have (putting them at 0) to get the item.<br>
<br>
4b.  If you are the only one of a certain class attending a raid and that class specific item drops, you do not need to spend points to get the item, but you will only recieve one point for the raid since you did not need to spend any.  This is to preserve a balance in the case of mutliclass drops.<br>
<br>
4c.  If it occurs that a raid produces such an amount of drops that everyone spends their points down to 0, the remaining drops will be randomed by those who want an item.<br>
<br>
4d.  If an item drops that no one wants to spend points on, it goes to general random by those who can and will use the item.  These items do not effect the ability to loot another item nor do they effect the amount of points a person has.  Raid leaders/loot coordinators have the right to use this rule with discresion to prevent people from just denying spending points on items to save their points and hope for winning a random on items.<br>
<br>
5. Plane of Growth would be its own point system since not everyone could go. It would be run with the same loot rules, 3 points per raid attended, 1 point per invite, highest gets priority when purchashing items. The point system would be as follows:<br>
<br>
Brestplate and legs=6 points<br>
All other pieces=2 points<br>
Weapons=3 points<br>
<br>
Post any questions, comments concerns or ideas, I will edit this proposal as new things are added or things are delted.  Lets try and get a new system in place, wether it be this one or a different one to get rid of the /random system.<br>
<br>
-Dinekus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uneaadan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Neaadan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#0000FF>(2/1/02 3:41:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fallianceraidforumfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.swbell.net/lhays/tun_me.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposed Loot System</span><hr size=1> This sounds like a good system.  Brenwyn and I were chatting about loot and came up with an idea.<br>
<br>
The people who lead raids gain a certain number of points.  We can alternate it between guilds.  The positions that would change would be loot cooridinator, whomever is in charge of groups, and whatever other positions we come up with.  This will encourage people to help out on the raids and take the burden off of the officers so much.<br>
<br>
Also what I'd like to see in effect until we get a system down in stone is we alternate loots.  What I mean is if DS gets a breastplate this round in Kael, then OOBS gets it next round.  This will 100% eliminate looting arguments and is 100% fair.  This would apply to all armors in all situations.<br>
<br>
